  "text": "Second derivatives were computed for NIR and mIR spectra. In the case of NIR, an orthogonal signal correction (OSC, see [CITATION_1] ) filter was applied once. ATR-mIR spectra were normalized to a total integral of 100, while NIR spectra were normalized using MSC. None of these normalization steps were applied to NMR spectra. Last, spectroscopic variables were scaled by their standard deviations (unit variance scaling a.k.a. autoscaling).",
